======================================================================
PHASE 1A: THE C3 FRUSTRATED POTENTIAL
======================================================================

  V(phi1,phi2,phi3) = +J * [cos(phi1-phi2) + cos(phi2-phi3) + cos(phi3-phi1)]
  J > 0: antiferromagnetic (repulsive) — phases want to separate

  V at 120-degree spacing:
    V = J * 3 * cos(2pi/3) = J * 3 * (-1/2) = -1.5
    = -3J/2 = -1.5
    VERIFIED: V(120) = -3J/2

  V at aligned (all same):
    V = J * 3 * cos(0) = 3.0
    = +3J

  For J > 0 (antiferromagnetic):
    V(120)    = -3J/2 = -1.5
    V(aligned)= +3J   = 3.0
    V(120) < V(aligned): True
    120-degree spacing IS the ground state for antiferromagnetic coupling

  Gradient at 120 degrees:
    dV/dphi1 = -J*[sin(-2pi/3) + sin(2pi/3)] = 0.0
    VERIFIED: gradient = 0 (stationary point)

  Hessian diagonal at 120 degrees:
    d2V/dphi1^2 = 1.0
    Positive (J>0): True
    VERIFIED: local minimum

  Zero-magnetization test:
    Re(sum e^{i*phi_k}) = -1.336382355e-51
    Im(sum e^{i*phi_k}) = 1.336382355e-51
    VERIFIED: sum = 0 (zero magnetization)

  PHASE 1A SUMMARY:
    The frustrated XY model on a triangle with J > 0 has
    ground state at 120-degree equal spacing.
    This is the Koide angular structure.
    Known result (textbook frustrated magnetism).
    New connection: Koide parametrization = zero-magnetization condition.

